        <p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Huyton sits at the eastern edge of the Liverpool city boundary, bordering Knowsley, and has a diverse housing stock reflecting several decades of development. The area has substantial post-war social housing built in the 1950s and 1960s, much of which has since been sold under right-to-buy and is now privately owned, alongside newer private estates developed in the 1980s and 1990s near Huyton town centre.

Post-war L36 properties from the 1950s have original copper pipework and heating systems that are now 60 to 70 years old. Pinhole leaks, corroded cylinder connections and failing pump seals are all common in this housing stock. The newer 1980s private estates have plumbing from that era   mostly copper with compression fittings   now 40 years old and beginning to show wear. We carry a comprehensive range of repair parts for both eras of housing. Huyton landlords can use our <a href="/gas-safety-certificate-liverpool" style="color:var(--orange);font-weight:700;">gas safety certificate</a> service for L36 rental properties, and we offer <a href="/power-flushing-liverpool" style="color:var(--orange);font-weight:700;">power flushing</a> for systems with sludge-related cold radiator problems.</p>
